<Author>GlobeGirly
<Content>Good Hotel  As we walked onto Pintor Fortuny, we passed the very posh Hotel 1898 on our left and the even posher Le Meridien on our right, before approaching our hotel, Silken Ramblas (apparently also known as Ambassador Hotel). Pleasantly surprised, the hotel looked exactly how the web photos portrayed it; modern and simple with an above average and somewhat superior feel to it. Parts of the hotel is constructed in line with Barcelona's famous architectural heritage which was nice to see. The rooms were sizeable with a flatscreen TV and powerful hairdryer. Our air conditioning and fridge did not work however, although our friends' did work fine. Be warned that they do not have an iron and ironing board available for customers, and if you need something ironed you have to ask housekeeping to do it - apparently it is their policy for safety reasons, but at around 10 Euros a pop, I'm not so sure! The best thing about the room was undoubtedly the larger than average double bed which was extremely comfortable and spacious for two! The bathroom was not top notch, but was modern and clean. The shower was not the newest of showers, but the shower head was great. The hotel bar was small and arranged in an open plan area but offered quite a good range of and cocktails which were about 7-9 Euros per cocktail, and very well made. Location was fab - literally just 1 minute from the Ramblas. Overall a very nice hotel and very reasonably priced - I would stay again. 
