<Author>jellyfish11
<Content>Above average hotel with nice pool. This was my first visit to Barcelona, and I stayed here for six nights. When we arrived, we were told our room had been upgraded to a Silken Room. We were told this meant it had a double bed rather than two single beds pushed together. When we booked through the hotel website, I had requested a nice room because it was a birthday trip to the city - maybe this was the reason for the upgraded room, and was a positive start to my impressions of the hotel.The room we were given was on the first floor. It had a small balcony,just enough to stand on, overlooking the side street that the hotel is on. The room appeared clean and tidy and had a sofa bed as well as the double bed. The bathroom had limited lighting and the shower was even darker! The shower was over the bath, but a nice walk-in shower could easily be installed if the bidet's were removed. While getting ready to go out on our first night, we discovered the hairdryer didn't work. With wet hair, my friend made a quick call to reception and they informed us we would have to wait 1/2 hour until someone could come and have a look. We said we could not wait that long and wanted a replacement more quickly. Five minutes later, we had a new hairdryer. The bed was a double, but there are two separate duvet covers.The pool on the hotel roof was just what was needed after lots of walking around the city. However, there are only nine sunbeds and hotel has over a hundred rooms!!! I found myself choosing between lying on the floor, or on the wooden decking that covered what was once a jacuzzi pool. The hotel will supply a towel for the pool for a deposit of 10 euro each.Over the course of our stay, we noticed that the large mirror in the room had not been cleaned at all (we had swatted some insects on it!) and there was a layer of dust on the pannelled walls. Apart from that, it seemed to be reasonably clean.We didn't eat at the hotel but were able to get hot drinks from the bar, When we wanted a coffee in the morning, the bar was shut, but we were able to get someone from the dining room to come and make us what we wanted, without any fuss.We didn't make use of the mini bar as there is a supermarket just around the corner where we were able to stock up on Spanish beers very cheaply!The hotel is in a good location and there are nice bars and restaurants in the area. 
