<Content>Honeymooning in The Silken Ramblas My new wife and I, Mrs LeChefCymru took our honeymoon at this Hotel in Barcelona. All I can say is what a very modern cool hotel, well situated, just off La Rambla in a small side street literally 150m from Placa de Catalunya. This was perfect as we took the Aerobus directly from the airport straight to Placa de Catalunya and we just had a very short walk with our cases.Anyway back to the hotel, the reception was very modern in dark woods and marble and led straight into the lobby bar. We didn't use that because of the abundance of bars in Barcelona but it looked nice all the same, just a little quiet. The reception staff were freindly and professional.We had a standard room which was air conditioned, had a large bed, sofa, TV, dressing area and good bath/shower. The room was immaculate and again very contemporary. A nice touch to my mind was the constant 'chillout' music available if you should so wish. Also, the room was toward the rear of the hotel so we did not get much of the street noise.On the roof was a nice terrace with great views and a compact swimming pool, you could order drinks from the bar if you wanted via a telephone.There is a gym but this was very limited to one bench with a light barbell and a stationery bike.We did not take breakfast at the Hotel as there was a good little cafe in the adjacent square which did a nice bocadillo. We did not eat in the hotel at all as there are plenty of good eateries in Barcelona, most of which you will find in the narrow side streets off La Rambla.All in all a fantastic honeymoon complimented by a good quality hotel in a good location 
