<Author>VanGoghIII
<Content>Not at all bad! First of all, when we read of other reviews mentioning the noise intrusion from other rooms, we were aprehensive but the rest of the hotel sounded like the kind of thing we were looking for, so we risked it. I'm glad we did as there was no problem for us, with any noise whatsoever. I'm not saying it isn't possible in other rooms, but one can only speak as one finds, and we had no issues with noise.The staff were pretty friendly, but my wife and I are the kind of people who like to be friendly, and use some words in the local language and that usually improves relations with all but the most obnoxious locals! The staff were helpful as before leaving home we emailed a couple of times, and rang, just to confirm bookings etc. After arrival, we were pleased with our room, which had a view onto apleasant side street, and staff were helpful in pointing out local tourist sites, booking local shows, and warning about the local crime hotspots and techniques. We personally experienced nothing bad, but were on our guard most of the time. The hotel bar is nice, we always had helpful staff there, on the few occaisions when we just felt like a cocktail. There are some terrificsmall bars and cafes within easy walking distance, without ever goingnear La Rambla. We were going to buy the Barcelona card for travel around the city but there was no need for one, as everything is virtually walking distance, or just get the carnet of 10 tickets for the odd time you want to use a metro or the cable car. The hotel concierge recomended a particular Flamenco show nearby witha buffet before the show included in the price, and I have to say that this was excellent, well worth seeing, and the waiters were goodfun. The Hard Rock Cafe was actually enjoyable too, not at all like the London one, much more fun. Try and use a few words of Spanish, itdefinitely got us better service there. The gym was not available whilst we were staying at this hotel, but the pool on the roof was excellent. I used this everyday, and loved it. I really had a pleasant holiday here in Barcelona, and the hotel and its location helped a great deal with that. Bonne Vaccences. 
